description: Erection of building comprising of various heights up to  a maximum of 29 storeys above a podium block (comprising of upper ground, ground and lower ground levels) to accommodate 295 residential units; 674sq.m of mixed use commercial floor space (use classes A1, A2, A3, A4, A5 and B1); underground car park for upto 81 cars and ancillary plant room.
decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  Prior to construction an amended sustainability report shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority and shall be implemented and retained thereon to the satisfaction of the Local Planning Authority.  This report shall show how the following can be achieved:
-The development hereby approved will achieve at least a 'Very Good' rating under the BREEAM (BRE Environmental Assessment Method) Ecohomes Scheme.  This rating shall be achieved at all stages of the development.   
-Carbon Indexing of the residential units will be an average of 8.6, with 8.0 as a minimum. 
-Detailed calculations for determining the Carbon Index and BRE's Ecohomes rating shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. 
-10% of all operational energy consumption to be derived from on site renewable sources. 
        
REASON:  To promote sustainability and energy efficiency.
